title: For Sale:  HK USP Compact .45- 50th Anniversary Model- German
postcontent:
A rare HK USP Compact .45 for sale.  This is a 50th Anniversary model.  It is in pristine condition but has exactly 50 rounds fired through it to test reliability.  I bought it because I love the USP Compacts and the reliability/accuracy.  I wanted an original all German HK and something a bit more unique and special than just a regular USP Compact.  It was to be a bedside gun but I need to sell because I simply have collected too many now.

It has been converted to LEM (medium) so has a smooth and consistent trigger pull.  It is not overly light since I am more concerned about safety and real-world use.  All my HKs are LEM and if you have not tried it, you should.  It is similar to a Kahr trigger in concept...and a lot safer than a Glock trigger.  It can be converted back to DA/SA (or a light LEM) with just some part interchange.  I probably have all the original parts.

These go for around $1,000 - $1,200.  The LEM conversion was done by Bill Springfield- considered to be the best in the business.  That costs about $160.  Here is your chance to own a real German HK from 1999/2000.  It does have a high-gloss blued finish and has never been holstered or carried.  It comes in a wooden case with a HK badge/coin, and the wooden case can be locked with two golden keys.  There is also a cardboard HK case.

Can meet in the Littleton or DTC area.  Cash only.  No felons, and it must be legal for you to own a gun in Colorado.  CO Driver's License or CCW required for proof of residency.  

No trades please.

title: For Sale:  SKS with every tactical mod imaginable
postcontent:
For sale is one of the most tactical SKS' you're likely to see listed for a long time...

This started as a 59/66a1 Yugo SKS.  It was a shooter when I got her, however, I saw more potential.  This is how this project ran away ? -for nearly 6mo of building/trying/re-trying/buying/fitting, you get the point. 

Barrel was shortened to just over 16” (mind you this is done by a qualified gunsmith and a machinist).  End re-threaded to 14x1LH.   PWS muzzlebreak is chosen http://primaryweapons.com/store/pc/viewPrd.asp?idproduct=57.  Gas selector is fine tuned by adding a gasket (no problems switching from semi to single shot or vice versa). Extra Stainless Steel Gas Valve is purchased http://www.milsurpstuff.com/proddetail.asp?prod=MSKSGV1 (included in the case).  Tapco furniture is dumped and replaced by an ATI folder set http://www.amazon.com/Ultimate-Professional-Aluminum-Upgrade-Package/dp/B003BRDAKQ.  ATI sling added http://www.amazon.com/Advanced-Technology-59584-Nylon-Sling/dp/B003Y3KBE0/ref=sr_1_1?s=sporting-goods&ie=UTF8&qid=REDACTED&sr=1-1.  .  Bi-pod added http://www.amazon.com/UTG-Tactical-Metal-Adjustable-Height/dp/B003M4OY0I/ref=sr_1_9?s=sporting-goods&ie=UTF8&qid=REDACTED&sr=1-9.  Extended mag release added http://www.midwayusa.com/product/137430/tapco-extended-magazine-release-sks-plastic-black?cm_mmc=Froogle-_-Gunsmithing+-+Gun+Parts+-+Rifle+-+%28Aftermarket%29-_-PriceCompListing-_-137430 Firefield 1.5x-5x with dual lit adjustable reticles + green laser dot added http://www.sportsmansguide.com/net/cb/firefield-15-5x32-mm-green-laser-rifle-scope-matte-black.aspx?a=713605 .  Replacement receiver mount is tweaked to hold zero, however, eventually aluminum rail isn't reliable enough and a Choate Mount is mounted http://www.midwayusa.com/product/435151/choate-scope-mount-sks-steel-blue . Choate had to be drilled and tapped with/to 8/40 thread – done by a machinist again.  In the process ATI stock was modified to accept extra width of the Choate mount – that was done.  Choate does not have adequate slots to accept Firefield scope (it was designed for the weaver rings) – machine work is performed to slot Choate to accommodate Firefield scope/laser.  This is all in a Pelican 1720 case http://www.amazon.com/Pelican-1720-Case-Foam-Black/dp/B0014D68DK/ref=pd_sim_sbs_sg_5 .  Prince’s Paratrooper front sights were added and sighted, so Irons can be used http://www.assaultplanet.com/products/sks-accessories/ .  Murray firing pin with spring added to the bolt http://www.murraysguns.com/sksown.htm (extra spring included in the fancy case). 4 Tapco 5rd magazines (these are IMPOSSIBLE to find so I can’t even link it, but these do pop up on ebay for $40-50ish each) purchased.  5 Tapco 20rd black magazines purchased http://www.midwayusa.com/product/862913/tapco-magazine-sks-762x39mm-russian-20-round-polymer?cm_mmc=Froogle-_-Gunsmithing+-+Magazines+-+Rifle+-+11%2b+Rounds-_-PriceCompListing-_-862913 .  Forward fancy grip purchased and added http://www.amazon.com/UTG-Combat-Foregrip-Concealed-Compartment/dp/B003TWX9EA/ref=sr_1_33?s=sporting-goods&ie=UTF8&qid=REDACTED&sr=1-33. Broken shell extractor purchased and added to the case along with a shell deflector and front sight adjustment tool plus an interim scope mount with rings (while Choate was in transit)….
All in all: $360 SKS originally, almost $500 in machining/gunsmithing costs, Pelican case is $200, magazines are $200, muzzlebreak $100, scope/laser $150, Choate mount $40, ATI furniture+Grip+bipod+other accessories $300+.  Front sights, gas valve, murry spring = $100.  20rd magazines are loaded with a 125gr Silver Bear Soft Points.  5rd Magazines are with 125gr Golden Bear 

You're looking at $2,000 "all in" for what's up for sale.

I'm asking $995 in a face to face sale.  No checks, as I'm sure you can appreciate.

 You'll provide the info for me to complete a bill of sale.  Yes, it's more than 922r compliant, no worries there.  Before thinking of a "how about-(insert lowball offer) ask yourself when's the last time you saw a deal where you were getting a discount of OVER 50%?

I'm in the Milwaukee area, I'd be willing, at a mutually convenient time, to go as far north as Fon du Lac, as far west as Johnson Creek, and as far south as the xway around Racine if that helps you out.

With all the photos I think you'll get a very complete idea of what's being offered, feel free to email with any questions.  Thanks for looking.

postcontent: Every week I see morons on here selling new AR rifles with collapsible stocks, flash suppressors and bayonet lugs. These are COMPLETELY ILLEGAL in the state of NY on a rifle made after 1994. Either these people are inexperienced idiots, undercover cops or knowingly selling something illegal. So when you see an ad that says "Brand new Bushmaster with collapsible stock blah blah blah" know that this is ILLEGAL. How adult men with these types of weapons don't know the New York State assault weapons ban law is beyond me. BE CAREFUL and know the law! On a new AR type rifle you MUST have a pinned stock, NOT A COLLAPSIBLE ONE, a muzzle brake and NOT a flash suppressor and you CANNOT have a bayonet lug. It must be removed. These are felonies in the state of New York. Educate yourself before you buy from some of these idiots.
